properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Access for Type 2 road trains - BROKEN HILL, COBAR AND BOURKE Barrier Highway, Kidman Way and Mitchell Highway to QLD border
properties.otherAdvice:
Type 2 Road Trains up to 53.5 metres to temporarily travel through Broken Hill, Cobar and Burke    

Due to flooding in central Australia closing access from the southern states to the Northern Territory along the Stuart Highway and Birdsville Track:

  • Road trains up to 53.5 metres in length have been granted temporary access on the Barrier Highway from the South Australian border through Broken Hill to Cobar, on Kidman Way to Bourke, and on the Mitchell Hwy to the Queensland border.  

Traffic control will be in place to support the safe movement of these large heavy vehicles at:         

  • Broken Hill - the corner of Iodide and Williams streets and Iodide and Argent streets
  • Cobar - the corner of Barton Street and Barrier Highway

Type 2 Road Trains are restricted to travelling at 90 km/hr.  All other vehicles are advised to overtake with caution due to the length of the vehicles.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Royal National Park precincts at capacity - ROYAL NATIONAL PARK Sir Bertram Stevens Drive
properties.otherAdvice:
Road closures will be in place as precincts and car parks within the Royal National Park, including Wattamolla Beach, Garie Beach, Audley, Maianbar and Bundeena, reach capacity.

Visitors are encouraged to check the Royal National Park local alerts before travelling for updates on precinct access.

Road closures when precincts reach capacity:

  • Wattamolla Rd between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Wattamolla Beach is now CLOSED
  • Garie Rd between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Garie Beach
  • Bonnie Vale
  • Garawarra Farm carpark (including the carpark for Figure 8 Pools)
  • Maianbar Rd between Bundeena Dr and Maianbar township
  • Bundeena Dr between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Bundeena township (traffic controllers and NSW Police will be on site at Maianbar Rd and Bundeena Dr managing access for local residents, upon proof of address).
